Never ❌ do these 7 things in GOA 🏖️

1️⃣ Don’t visit too popular beaches in Goa like Baga, Anjuna etc which are flooded with tourists and everything is expensive there. Many pickpockets and scammers roam on these beaches

2️⃣ Don’t take cabs as they are insanely expensive. The taxi cost is like ₹100 per km. Rent a scooty instead which will cost 300-500 per day depending upon the season.

3️⃣ Wear proper dress (Indian clothes preferably) if you are planning to visit temple as shorts are not allowed there. Respect the rules and follow them.

4️⃣ If planning to visit Church, wear long dresses. Dont wear short dresses or shorts as they wont allow you to enter the church. Do follow the rules!

5️⃣ Don’t throw trash, beer bottles, plastic etc on the beaches. Let’s protect Goa’s natural beauty. Please don’t litter on the beaches.

6️⃣ If riding a scooty always wear helmet. It is necessary for the driver but not for passenger. The fines are hefty if you get caught riding scooty without helmet.

7️⃣ Don’t go to Goa with the mentality that “yahan toh sab chalta hai”. Take good care of yourself, the surroundings, the places and most importantly respect people and the locals.

BONUS POINT 

8️⃣ Don’t forget to ENJOY! 
.
.
.
